      "title": "The Secret Language of Animals",
      "level": "beginner",
      "levelcefr": "A2",
      "cover": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1456926631375-92c8ce872def?w=600&h=400&fit=crop",
      "coverType": "image",
      "sound": "",
      "author": "Nature Explorer",
      "dictionaries": ["../Dictionarys/main.json"],
      "content": [
        "Max was a quiet boy who loved animals. He spent most of his time in the forest behind his house. While other children played games, Max watched animals. He noticed something interesting. Animals communicated with each other.",
        "Birds had different songs for different messages. Squirrels flicked their tails to warn about danger. Rabbits thumped their feet when they were scared. Max started to write notes about animal communication.",
        "One rainy afternoon, Max found a hurt baby bird. The bird had fallen from its nest. Its wing was broken. Max carefully picked up the bird. He brought it home and made a small nest from a shoebox.",
        "Max's mother helped him care for the bird. They fed it with an eyedropper. They kept it warm with soft cloths. Max talked to the bird every day. He named it Chirpy. Chirpy slowly got better.",
        "After two weeks, Chirpy's wing was healed. Max took him back to the forest. He placed Chirpy on a tree branch. But something strange happened. Chirpy didn't fly away immediately.",
        "Instead, Chirpy chirped a special song. Max listened carefully. The song sounded like 'thank you.' Other birds joined in the song. Soon, the whole forest was filled with beautiful bird songs.",
        "From that day, Max could understand animal language. Squirrels told him where to find the best nuts. Rabbits showed him secret paths in the forest. Deer warned him about approaching storms.",
        "One day, the animals gave Max an important message. A big storm was coming. The storm would be very dangerous. Max ran home and told his parents. At first, they didn't believe him.",
        "But Max was very serious. He explained what the animals had told him. His parents decided to prepare just in case. They secured the house. They stored extra food and water.",
        "That night, the storm arrived. It was the biggest storm in fifty years. Trees fell down. Roads flooded. But Max's family was safe. Their house was well prepared.",
        "After the storm, everyone in the village was amazed. How did Max know about the storm? Max told them about animal communication. At first, people laughed. But then they started to listen.",
        "Max became the village's weather predictor. Animals told him about coming weather changes. Farmers asked him about the best planting times. Fishermen asked about sea conditions.",
        "Max started a nature club for children. He taught them how to understand animals. He showed them how to respect nature. The children learned to listen to the forest.",
        "Years passed. Max grew up and became a wildlife expert. He wrote books about animal communication. He gave talks around the world. But he always returned to his forest.",
        "The forest was his first teacher. The animals were his first friends. And Chirpy, now a father many times over, still visited him every morning. Their friendship lasted a lifetime."
      ],
      "wordCount": 502,
      "audio": null,
      "translations": {}
